{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB2728", "title": "Groundwater: de minimis extractors: fees: exemption.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Groundwater", "deminimisextractors", "exemption", "fees"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law authorizes a groundwater sustainability agency to impose fees, including, but not limited to, permit fees and fees on groundwater extraction or other regulated activity, to fund the costs of a groundwater sustainability program, and investigations, inspections, compliance assistance, enforcement, and program administration, as provided. Existing law prohibits a groundwater sustainability agency from imposing those fees on a de minimis extractor, as defined, unless the agency has regulated the user, as provided.\n\nThis bill would authorize a local government, including, but not limited to, a groundwater sustainability agency, that imposes a fee, levy, charge, or exaction for groundwater monitoring or management, upon making specified findings, to exempt de minimis extractors, including the above-described regulated users, from the payment of the fee, levy, charge, or exaction, as provided."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Open and Transparent Water Data Act."}, {"note": "", "title": "Water delivery infrastructure."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab2728"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-20", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 23.", "date": "2026-02-21", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on W., P., & W.", "date": "2026-03-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral